    {
      "name": "End-to-End Workflow",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "1. Setup - Create Test Driver in DB",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "-- Run this SQL in Supabase to create a test driver\nINSERT INTO drivers (name, phone, email, vehicle_type, license_number, org_id, status)\nVALUES ('Test Driver', '+1234567890', 'test@example.com', 'van', 'DL123456', 1, 'pending_activation')\nON CONFLICT (phone) DO UPDATE SET status = 'pending_activation';"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "https://supabase.com/",
              "protocol": "https",
              "host": [
                "supabase.com"
              ]
            },
            "description": "First, create a test driver in your Supabase database. Go to Supabase SQL Editor and run this query."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "2. Request OTP",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"phone\": \"+1234567890\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/drivers/auth/request-otp",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "drivers",
                "auth",
                "request-otp"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Step 1: Request OTP. You should get a 200 response with 'OTP sent' message."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "3. Get OTP Code",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "https://supabase.com/",
              "protocol": "https",
              "host": [
                "supabase.com"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Step 2: Get the OTP code\n\nOptions:\nA) Check Supabase logs:\n   - Go to Supabase Dashboard > Logs\n   - Search for your phone number\n   - Find the OTP code being sent\n\nB) Check SMS inbox (if real SMS provider configured)\n   - Check your phone SMS messages\n   - Find the OTP code\n\nC) Check Inbucket (if using Supabase local dev with docker)\n   - Go to http://localhost:54324/\n   - Look for OTP in email preview\n\nCopy the 6-digit OTP code for the next step."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "4. Verify OTP",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"phone\": \"+1234567890\",\n  \"otp\": \"123456\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/drivers/auth/verify-otp",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "drivers",
                "auth",
                "verify-otp"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Step 3: Verify OTP with the code from step 2. Replace '123456' with the actual OTP code."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "5. Verify Results in Database",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "https://supabase.com/",
              "protocol": "https",
              "host": [
                "supabase.com"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Step 4: Verify the login worked by checking the database:\n\nRun this SQL query:\n\n```sql\nSELECT id, name, phone, phone_verified_at, user_id, status \nFROM drivers \nWHERE phone = '+1234567890';\n```\n\nExpected:\n- phone_verified_at: Should be set to current timestamp\n- user_id: Should be populated with a UUID\n- status: Should be 'active' (auto-activated on first login)"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
